en_72558_0	The UN’s special rapporteur on the human rights of internally displaced persons Dr. Chalokaa Beyaani is scheduled to arrive in the island today.
en_72558_1	Resettlement Ministry Secretary Janaka Sugathadaasa said while the UN special representative would remain in the country for six days, he was scheduled to meet people displaced due to the war.
en_72558_2	In addition he will hold discussions with several Government Ministers including Foreign Minister G. L. Peiris.
en_72558_3	While the UN’s special representative is scheduled to tour the North and Mullaitiv, he is also due to inspect the relief camps.
